t = int(input())
for _ in range(t):
    inp = input().split()
    n = int(inp[0])
    player = 0 if inp[1] == 'Dee' else 1
    moves = [0, 0]
    for _ in range(n):
        stack = input()
        if stack[0] != stack[-1]:
            continue
        moves[int(stack[0])] += 1
    winner = player
    if moves[player] > moves[1 - player]:
        winner = 1 - player
    print('Dee' if winner == 0 else 'Dum')
